correctness.rationale: Multiple schema and factual issues are present despite some correct entries (PEALD method, precursors/co-reactant, 200 °C, 1.2 Torr≈mmHg, 300 W plasma, substrates, 20 nm thickness, TFT structure, and device metrics within the reported ranges). Key problems: (1) Invalid/empty values violating schema: many quantityValue.numericValue fields are set to None (not valid JSON and not numbers) across growthPerCycle.values, numberofCycles, nucleationPeriod, coReactant dosingTime, all purgeTime entries, all flowRates, optical/electrical properties (bandGap, resistivity, carrierDensity, mobility), uniformity.variation, conformality.aspectRatio, roughness.value, filmDensity.value, onOffRatio. These must be numeric or omitted if optional; here many are required within their sections. (2) Unit errors: precursor dosing times are reported in the article as seconds (DADI 1.5 s, TMGa 0.1 s, DEZ 0.1 s) but encoded with unit MilliSEC and numeric values 1.5/0.1/0.1 (i.e., 1.5 ms/0.1 ms/0.1 ms). They should be 1500, 100, 100 ms. Subthreshold swing is given as 0.24 V decade^-1 in the article but encoded as 0.24 with unit MilliV (0.24 mV). It should be 240 mV (or use V with 0.24 if the schema allowed). (3) Placeholders not traceable: 'Not Found' is used for carrierGas, purgingGas, reactor name/manufacturer, deliveryMethod, roughness characterization method. This violates the no-empty/traceability requirement; carrier/purge gases are not stated in the article and should not be filled with placeholders (or should be supported if inferred, e.g., Ar, but the article does not explicitly state purge gas type). (4) Supercycle/composition coherence: supercycleDesign.numberofSubcycles counts are None; the atomicRatio is given as a range (0.56–0.63:0.13–0.17:0.17–0.34), not a single ratio for a specific process. The article reports many compositions (L1/L2 tie lines and an optimum region); the extraction collapses these into one process with mixed values, violating semantic coherence and the requirement to extract multiple distinct processes or one clearly defined sample. (5) Unsupported assertions: saturation is set to True without explicit support in the text; filmStability True is asserted broadly. Properties to correct/review: replace all None with valid numbers or remove optional fields; fix time and SS units; populate or omit carrier/purging gas with text-grounded values; provide a specific atomic ratio (and corresponding subcycle counts) per process and split into multiple processes if needed; remove/justify saturation; add measured material properties (e.g., film density values reported for representative samples) if tying to a specific sample.

completeness.rationale: Several required or populated fields violate the schema or are incomplete/non-traceable. Numerous numericValue entries are null where the schema requires numbers (e.g., growthPerCycle values, numberofCycles, nucleationPeriod, dosingTime coReactant times, purgeTime, flowRates, elementalConcentration, uniformity variation, conformality aspectRatio, roughness, filmDensity). Use of placeholder strings ("Not Found") for required fields (carrierGas, purgingGas; reactor info; deliveryMethod; roughness method) is not traceable to the article and undermines completeness. Units are inconsistent: precursor dose times are reported in seconds in the article (1.5 s for DADI; 0.1 s for TMGa/DEZ) but encoded with unit MilliSEC without conversion; SS is given as 0.24 V dec−1 in the article but encoded as 0.24 with unit MilliV (should be 240 mV). Supercycle design lacks numeric subcycle counts (a:b:c) even though the article defines supercycles; extraction should either provide explicit counts for representative compositions or represent multiple processes. Material properties lack available quantitative data from the paper: band gap values (ranges for L1/L2 are given), carrier density thresholds/regions, and several film densities (e.g., Ga_4 5.40 g cm−3, In_1 6.90 g cm−3, etc.) are reported but not captured. Device properties are partially captured (μ_FE, V_TH) but omit on/off ratio and encode SS with the wrong unit; the mobility is given as a single value despite the article providing a range (41.4–43.7 cm^2 V−1 s−1). While some core items are correct (PEALD method, precursors/co-reactant, 200 °C, 1.2 Torr, 300 W, substrates, 20 nm film for TFT), the overall extraction is incomplete and contains schema/units issues. To improve: (1) replace nulls with actual numeric values where reported (convert dosing times to ms; set SS to 240 mV), (2) set carrier/purging gas to Ar if justified by the Ar/O2 plasma or omit optional fields rather than "Not Found" where allowed, (3) add supercycle subcycle counts or multiple processes for representative compositions, (4) add quantitative band gap, carrier density, and film density values reported, (5) supply purge times/flow rates only if available; otherwise adjust modeling to avoid populating with nulls, and (6) ensure all units are QUDT-compliant and correctly converted.
